Princesse Maud of Wales

Princesse Maud of Wales. A daughter of King Edward VII and granddaughter of Queen Victoria, Princess Maud of Wales (1869-1938) became Queen Consort of Norway when her husband, Prince Carl of Denmark, who she married in 1896, ascended the Norwegian throne as Haakon VII in 1906.
